            <section ID="splSectionDescription">
               <id root="6ba255d3-c067-4545-a2ec-5db23fd07703"/>
               <code code="34089-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title mediaType="text/x-hl7-title+xml">
DESCRIPTION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>IOPIDINE 1% Ophthalmic Solution contains apraclonidine hydrochloride, an alpha adrenergic agonist, in a sterile isotonic solution for topical application to the eye. Apraclonidine hydrochloride is a white to off-white powder and is highly soluble in water. Its chemical name is 2-[(4-amino-2,6 dichlorophenyl)imino] imidazolidine monohydrochloride with an empirical formula of C<sub>9</sub>H<sub>11</sub>Cl<sub>3</sub>N<sub>4</sub> and a molecular weight of 281.6.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>The chemical structure of apraclonidine hydrochloride is:</paragraph>
                  <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="chemical"/>
                  <paragraph>Each mL of IOPIDINE 1% Ophthalmic Solution contains: <content styleCode="bold">Actives: </content>apraclonidine hydrochloride 11.5 mg equivalent to apraclonidine base 10 mg. <content styleCode="bold">Inactives: </content>sodium chloride, sodium acetate, sodium hydroxide and/or hydrochloric acid (pH 4.4-7.8), purified water and benzalkonium chloride 0.01% (preservative). Osmolality is 260-320 mOsm.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20180301"/>
